# Text Data Compliance Checker – Walkthrough

## Overview

Built a complete text data compliance checking module at `compliance-checker/text/` — 31 files implementing a 10-step pipeline (A→J), packaged as a FastAPI microservice with Docker deployment.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["A: Source Intake"] --> B1["B1: Source Classification"]
    B1 --> B2a["B2a: TruffleHog Secrets"]
    B1 --> B2b["B2b: ScanCode Licenses"]
    B1 --> C["C: Text Extract (DataTrove)"]
    C --> D["D: Dedup (MinHash)"]
    D --> E1a["E1a: Keyword Scan (FlashText2)"]
    D --> E1b["E1b: Regex Scan (Hyperscan)"]
    D --> F["F: PII Detection (Presidio)"]
    F --> G["G: Safety (Qwen3Guard)"]
    B2a & B2b & E1a & E1b & F & G --> H["H: Evidence Aggregation"]
    H --> I["I: Policy Decision (OPA)"]
    I --> J["J: Lineage (OpenLineage)"]

    style A fill:#4CAF50,color:#fff
    style I fill:#F44336,color:#fff
    style J fill:#2196F3,color:#fff
```

